name: Golden Eagle
description: The golden eagle is one of the best-known birds of prey in the Northern Hemisphere. It is a large, dark brown raptor with a wingspan of up to 2.3 meters.

name: Bald Eagle
description: The bald eagle is a bird of prey found in North America. It is the national bird and symbol of the United States of America.

name: Peregrine Falcon
description: The peregrine falcon is renowned for its speed, reaching over 320 km/h (200 mph) during its characteristic hunting stoop (high-speed dive).

name: Harpy Eagle
description: The harpy eagle is a powerful raptor and one of the largest and most powerful predatory birds. It has a distinctive feathered crown and a strong bill.

name: Kingfisher
description: Kingfishers are small to medium-sized, brightly colored birds with short tails and long, sharp bills. They are known for their fishing skills and vibrant plumage.
